	<p><strong>Ravishankar Rajaraman</strong></p> 
	<p></p> 
	<p>A trailblazing group of 20 finally took off on a long overdue tour to break the monotony of office life and run away from the cacophony of Chennai streets.  Details of the trip follow...</p> 
	<p>Departure: 8:00 pm on 4<sup>th</sup> July by train to Podanur Junction, Coimbatore</p> 
	<p>Arrival at Valparai: 9:00 am on 5<sup>th</sup> July</p> 
	<p>Places visited:</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst">1.      Indira Gandhi Wildlife Sanctuary and National Park</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">2.      Monkey Falls</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">3.      Aliyar Dam</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">4.      Lome's Viewpoint</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">5.      Nirar and Sholayar Dam</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">6.      Nallamudi Poonjolai View Point</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">7.      Chitti Vinayagar Temple</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">8.      Number Parai</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpLast">9.      Balaji Temple</p> 
	<p>Return to Chennai: 7:00 am on 7<sup>th</sup> July</p> 
	<p>Trip cost per person: Rs. 1450/-</p> 
	<p>Important points to note before visiting Valparai:</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst">1.      The place is still not tourism ready and this should be kept in mind. Good hotels and food are hard to find and the only one we found was Hotel Green Hills. A suitable alternative would be to try out one of the tea estate bungalows.</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">2.      Tea gardens look green, but they are not like walking through long blades of grass. Tea plants are thick and they do not smell like your morning cup of tea. In fact you will smell more fertilizer.</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">3.      Watch out for leeches, especially during rains. Carry some salt with you.</p> 
	<p class="ListParagraphCxSpLast">4.      Every place of interest is kilometres away from Valparai and considerable amount of time is spent in travelling. Hence proper planning is required.</p> 
